      • runBinningOnly

        public void runBinningOnly()
        Runs only the binning program, useful in demarcations. In the case of the original run requiring a value of omega, sigma, npop, etc. we use the run() function, we runs fred method and hillclimbing, but this method will give us only the binning data.

      • fullLike

        public FredOutVal fullLike(FredOutVal value)
        Runs the full likelihood, with only one data point involved. pre: out is the acinas input file, value is the best data point from the initial fred method run, sequenceVals. post: FredOutVal is the full likelihood value.
        Parameters:
        value - The binning data.
        Returns:
        FredOutVal containing the best value for hillclimbing with it's full likelihood.
